docs.abstract: Sundar Pichai, the chief executive of Google, appeared in court to defend his company against a landmark federal antitrust case.
docs.snippet: Sundar Pichai, the chief executive of Google, appeared in court to defend his company against a landmark federal antitrust case.
docs.lead_paragraph: As Google’s chief executive, Sundar Pichai, tells it, his company has always been on the side of consumers. It has paid billions to other industry giants, like Apple and Samsung, he said, to make sure Google’s internet search engine worked as well as it should on those companies’ devices.

headline.main: Google C.E.O. Says Tech Giant Has Improved the Web for All Consumers
headline.print_headline: Google Made Web Better, Chief Argues

byline.original: By Nico Grant and David McCabe

docs.abstract: Google has worried for years that Apple would one day expand its internet search technology, and has been working on ways to prevent that from happening.
docs.snippet: Google has worried for years that Apple would one day expand its internet search technology, and has been working on ways to prevent that from happening.
docs.lead_paragraph: For years, Google watched with increasing concern as Apple improved its search technology, not knowing whether its longtime partner and sometimes competitor would eventually build its own search engine.

headline.main: Inside Google’s Plan to Stop Apple From Getting Serious About Search
headline.print_headline: Inside Google’s Efforts to Undercut Apple’s Search Ambitions

docs.abstract: Martin Scorsese’s three-and-a-half-hour epic is the first of three high-profile movies the tech company will give wide theatrical releases in the coming months.
docs.snippet: Martin Scorsese’s three-and-a-half-hour epic is the first of three high-profile movies the tech company will give wide theatrical releases in the coming months.
docs.lead_paragraph: The box office results for Martin Scorsese’s new film, “Killers of the Flower Moon,” will be revealed on Sunday and analyzed by reporters and industry insiders. Did the movie perform well? Did it fall short? Did Leonardo DiCaprio’s inability to promote the film because of the actors’ strike ultimately mean fewer people went to see it?

headline.main: Apple’s New Film Strategy Debuts With ‘Killers of the Flower Moon’
headline.print_headline: With a Theatrical Release, Apple Debuts Its New Film Strategy

docs.abstract: A year after adding à la carte sales of audiobooks, Spotify is offering paying subscribers 15 hours of books a month.
docs.snippet: A year after adding à la carte sales of audiobooks, Spotify is offering paying subscribers 15 hours of books a month.
docs.lead_paragraph: Four years ago, Spotify’s business was stagnating. Apple had overtaken it as the top paid music service in the United States, losses were mounting and customer growth was slowing.

headline.main: Spotify Gave Subscribers Music and Podcasts. Next: Audiobooks.
headline.print_headline: Audiobooks Get a Boost On Spotify

byline.original: By Alexandra Alter and Tripp Mickle

docs.abstract: Mr. Stewart and Apple are parting ways because of creative differences over “The Problem,” people with knowledge of the decision said.
docs.snippet: Mr. Stewart and Apple are parting ways because of creative differences over “The Problem,” people with knowledge of the decision said.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jon Stewart’s show on Apple’s streaming service is abruptly coming to an end, according to several people with knowledge of the decision, the result of creative differences between the tech giant and the former “Daily Show” host.

headline.main: Jon Stewart’s Show on Apple Is Ending
headline.print_headline: Stewart’s Show On Apple TV+ Comes to an End

byline.original: By Benjamin Mullin, John Koblin and Tripp Mickle

docs.abstract: A federal trade agency ruled that some Apple devices infringe on patents held by other companies.
docs.snippet: A federal trade agency ruled that some Apple devices infringe on patents held by other companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple Inc. sells a lot of smart watches during the holidays, but this year its sales of most Apple Watch models may well drop 100 percent — to literally zero — the day after Christmas.

headline.main: The Patent Fight That Could Take Apple Watches Off the Market
headline.print_headline: The Reason Apple Watches May Soon Disappear

docs.abstract: As the government wraps up its case in the landmark monopoly trial, it has built a picture of how Google became dominant in online search — and the harms that it says resulted.
docs.snippet: As the government wraps up its case in the landmark monopoly trial, it has built a picture of how Google became dominant in online search — and the harms that it says resulted.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since Sept. 12., the Department of Justice and a group of state attorneys general have questioned more than 30 witnesses as they try to prove that Google broke antitrust laws, in a landmark monopoly trial that may affect the power of the technology industry.

headline.main: What the U.S. Has Argued in the Google Antitrust Trial
headline.print_headline: 2 Key Angles In U.S. Case Vs. Google

byline.original: By David McCabe, Cecilia Kang and Steve Lohr

docs.abstract: Chinese state media outlets say the Taiwanese factory giant is under investigation in four provinces. The company said it treated legal compliance as a “fundamental principle.”
docs.snippet: Chinese state media outlets say the Taiwanese factory giant is under investigation in four provinces. The company said it treated legal compliance as a “fundamental principle.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign and local companies in China are increasingly the targets of tax audits and other regulatory reviews, as local governments try to steady their finances by collecting more revenue.

headline.main: Foxconn, Apple’s Manufacturer in China, Is Said to Be Under Tax Audit
headline.print_headline: China’s Apple Contractor Under Tax Audit

docs.abstract: In this 2017 internal Google document, an executive compares the search ads business to that of selling cigarettes or drugs.
